#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/async-defer-await.md savings=2%
M||tx|---
M||titl|Defer Await Until Needed
M||impa|hi
M||impa|avoids blocking unused code paths
M||tags|async, await, conditional, op
M||tx|---
M|Defe|tx|Move `await` operations into the branches where they're actually used to avoid blocking code paths that don't need them.
M|Defe|**In|**
M|Defe|tx|```ts
M|Defe|asyn|string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|Defe|tx|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|Defe|tx|if (skipProcessing) {
M|Defe|tx|// Returns immediately but still waited for userData
M|Defe|retu|true }
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|// Only this branch uses userData
M|Defe|tx|return processUserData(userData)
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|```
M|Defe|**Co|**
M|Defe|tx|```ts
M|Defe|asyn|string, skipProcessing: boolean) {
M|Defe|tx|if (skipProcessing) {
M|Defe|tx|// Returns immediately w/o waiting
M|Defe|retu|true }
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|// Fetch only when needed
M|Defe|tx|const userData = await fetchUserData(userId)
M|Defe|tx|return processUserData(userData)
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|```
M|Defe|**An|**
M|Defe|tx|```ts
M|Defe|// I|always fetches permissions
M|Defe|asyn|string, userId: string) {
M|Defe|tx|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|Defe|tx|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|Defe|tx|if (!resource) {
M|Defe|retu|'Not found' }
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|Defe|retu|'Forbidden' }
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|// C|fetches only when needed
M|Defe|asyn|string, userId: string) {
M|Defe|tx|const resource = await getResource(resourceId)
M|Defe|tx|if (!resource) {
M|Defe|retu|'Not found' }
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|const permissions = await fetchPermissions(userId)
M|Defe|tx|if (!permissions.canEdit) {
M|Defe|retu|'Forbidden' }
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|return await updateResourceData(resource, permissions)
M|Defe|tx|}
M|Defe|tx|```
M|Defe|tx|This op is esp valuable when the skipped branch is frequently taken, or when the deferred operation is expensive.
M|Defe|tx|For `await getFlag()` combined w/ a cheap synchronous guard (`flag && someCondition`), see [Check Cheap Conditions Before Async Flags](./async-cheap-condition-before-await.md).